Package pmdd.components.properties

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    NodeProperty
    NODE PROPERTY This is the abstract class to represent node properties.
    PropertyAllDiff
    ALL DIFFERENT CONSTRAINT We simply store into a set the already taken values.
    PropertyAllDiff.Allocator
    The allocator that is in charge of the PropertyAllDiff type.
    When not specified, the allocator has an initial capacity of 16.
    PropertyAmong  
    PropertyAmong.Allocator
    The allocator that is in charge of the PropertyAmong type.
    When not specified, the allocator has an initial capacity of 16.
    PropertyGCC
    GLOBAL CARDINALITY CONSTRAINT We use an interval to represent the number of time a value is taken : [min, max].
    PropertyGCC.Allocator
    The allocator that is in charge of the PropertyGCC type.
    When not specified, the allocator has an initial capacity of 16.
    PropertySequence
    SEQUENCE CONSTRAINT We use a matrix to represent the couples (q, l, u) with q = the size of the sequence, l = lowerbound and u = upperbound.
    PropertySequence.Allocator
    The allocator that is in charge of the PropertySequence type.
    When not specified, the allocator has an initial capacity of 16.
    PropertySum
    SUM CONSTRAINT We use an interval to represents the [min, max] value of the sum.
    PropertySum.Allocator
    The allocator that is in charge of the PropertySum type.
    When not specified, the allocator has an initial capacity of 16.
    PropertySumDouble  
    PropertySumDouble.Allocator
    The allocator that is in charge of the PropertySumDouble type.
    When not specified, the allocator has an initial capacity of 16.
